4 HR____ COMMENDING LINDA HELLENA KAUFFELD WHITE UPON HER
5 RETIREMENT AS A MEDICAID NURSE II WITH THE MEDICAID AGENCY
6 OF THE STATE OF ALABAMA.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is with great pride and deep appreciation
9 that we recognize individuals who have unselfishly devoted
10 their lives to public service and the health of Alabamians
11 throughout this great state; and
12 WHEREAS, in 1967, Linda Hellena Kauffeld White
13 graduated from College of the Ozarks with a Bachelor's
14 degree in Elementary Education and began many years of
15 exemplary public service as a teacher, first at Paris
16 Elementary School in Arkansas and then at Catoma Elementary
17 School in Montgomery, Alabama; and
18 WHEREAS, capitalizing on her interest in health and
19 her natural talent for always serving others, she pursued a
20 nursing degree; she graduated from Arkansas Northeastern
21 College, formerly known as Mississippi County Community
22 College, in 1986, and the following year, she began working
23 as a nurse with HealthSouth in Montgomery; subsequently
24 trading in late nights for a new opportunity to promote
25 public health, Mrs. White joined the Medicaid Agency of the
26 State of Alabama as a Medicaid Nurse I and Field Nurse
27 Specialist in March of 1991; she later achieved a promotion
28 to Medicaid Nurse II; and
Page 1

to Medicaid Nurse II; and
HR320 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, throughout her notable tenure at Medicaid,
30 Mrs. White dutifully accomplished numerous tasks and
31 assisted providers in ensuring that quality health care was
32 available to all from Huntsville to Mobile; her diverse work
33 covered family planning and prenatal care, nurse midwives,
34 and maternal and pediatric health care; and
35 WHEREAS, logging hundreds of thousands of miles
36 throughout the state to conduct on-site visits with
37 providers, collect statistical data, verify data accuracy,
38 analyze and evaluate the Prenatal and Maternity Waiver
39 Program, assist in the orientation of new health care
40 providers, review sterilization waivers, and perform
41 post-payment review, Mrs. White's immeasurable contributions
42 in her role greatly enhanced Medicaid's credibility through
43 public relations and impacted countless lives through the
44 promotion and facilitation of premium health services; and
45 WHEREAS, receiving numerous promotions and accolades
46 throughout her career, Mrs. White's superiors have noted
47 that "she always went above and beyond her duties to
48 research and resolve claim issues that have likely saved the
49 agency thousands of dollars"; and that "Mrs. Linda has been
50 praised by numerous providers for her keen knowledge and
51 expertise with maternity billing"; and
52 WHEREAS, not only did Mrs. White contribute
53 professionally to the agency, she also invested in and
54 encouraged her community and others in need through her
55 generosity and fun-loving spirit that never met a stranger;
56 she would often be the first to belt out a rendition of
Page 2

she would often be the first to belt out a rendition of
HR320 INTRODUCED
57 "Happy Birthday" on someone's special day and would
58 coordinate the collection of money from coworkers to
59 purchase Christmas gifts and necessities for those who had
60 fallen on unfortunate circumstances; and
61 WHEREAS, Mrs. White effortlessly balanced her
62 professional life and work with her faith and devoted love
63 for her family; she was married to the late Don Gene White
64 for 48 years and has two children, Gina Metcalf (Mitch) and
65 Josh White; and three grandchildren, Casey Anderson, Austin
66 White, and Dalton George (Avery); and
67 WHEREAS, a faithful member of Thorington Road Baptist
68 Church, Mrs. White has put her strong faith in action by
69 serving as a Sunday school teacher, choir member, and youth
70 chaperone on many youth trips, where she always planned
71 skits and other shenanigans to bring about fun and laughter;
72 she traveled to Russia in 1996 to assist World Help in
73 distributing Bibles, health care products, and school
74 supplies; and
75 WHEREAS, Linda White's distinguished 35-year career
76 with the Medicaid Agency of the State of Alabama comes to a
77 close on April 1, 2026; however, her legacy of public
78 service, professionalism, compassion, and expertise, along
79 with her unique ability to significantly impact the lives of
80 others for the better with laughter and a smile, will live
81 on in perpetuity through the countless people she has
82 served; now therefore,
83 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
84 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That we hereby commend Linda Hellena
